abstract: Catalan separatists clashed with the police in streets in Barcelona ahead of a draw against Real Madrid.
snippet: Catalan separatists clashed with the police in streets in Barcelona ahead of a draw against Real Madrid.
lead_paragraph: One of the world’s most-watched soccer matches was played amid heavy security Wednesday night as the Spanish authorities sought to keep Catalonia’s separatist movement from disrupting the game between host Barcelona and Real Madrid.

abstract: Barcelona and Real Madrid played out a 0-0 draw for the first time in 17 years on Wednesday in a politically supercharged “clásico” match played amid a large separatist protest that turned violent outside Camp Nou stadium.
snippet: Barcelona and Real Madrid played out a 0-0 draw for the first time in 17 years on Wednesday in a politically supercharged “clásico” match played amid a large separatist protest that turned violent outside Camp Nou stadium.
lead_paragraph: BARCELONA, Spain — Barcelona and Real Madrid played out a 0-0 draw for the first time in 17 years on Wednesday in a politically supercharged “clásico” match played amid a large separatist protest that turned violent outside Camp Nou stadium.
headline_main: Barca Held 0-0 by Madrid Amid Separatist Protest at Camp Nou
headline_print_headline: Barca Held 0-0 by Madrid Amid Separatist Protest at Camp Nou

abstract: Panama declared a day of national mourning for Friday, the 30th anniversary of the U.S. invasion that ousted dictator Manuel Noriega and resulted in hundreds of deaths in the Central American nation.
snippet: Panama declared a day of national mourning for Friday, the 30th anniversary of the U.S. invasion that ousted dictator Manuel Noriega and resulted in hundreds of deaths in the Central American nation.
lead_paragraph: PANAMA CITY — Panama declared a day of national mourning for Friday, the 30th anniversary of the U.S. invasion that ousted dictator Manuel Noriega and resulted in hundreds of deaths in the Central American nation.
headline_main: Panama Declares Day of Mourning for US Invasion Anniversary
headline_print_headline: Panama Declares Day of Mourning for US Invasion Anniversary

abstract: Mayor Bill de Blasio engaged in “political horse trading,” holding back a report on the ultra-Orthodox schools, investigators found.
snippet: Mayor Bill de Blasio engaged in “political horse trading,” holding back a report on the ultra-Orthodox schools, investigators found.
lead_paragraph: Over four years ago, Mayor Bill de Blasio’s administration began a high-profile investigation into whether thousands of children in some ultra-Orthodox Jewish yeshivas were receiving basic secular education, including lessons on how to read and write in English.

abstract: She got her start in the 1940s as one of Rivera’s assistants. She went on to become a celebrated artist in both Mexico and her native Guatemala.
snippet: She got her start in the 1940s as one of Rivera’s assistants. She went on to become a celebrated artist in both Mexico and her native Guatemala.
lead_paragraph: In 1946, the Mexican muralist Diego Rivera invited Rina Lazo, one of his assistants, to have lunch at his home with him and his wife, the painter Frida Kahlo. Ms. Lazo was 23 and had been in Mexico for only a few months. She accepted.

abstract: A Wisconsin appeals court on Wednesday denied a request from the state Justice Department to immediately put on hold a judge's ruling to purge  more than 200,000 voter registrations in the key swing state before it hears from the other side.
snippet: A Wisconsin appeals court on Wednesday denied a request from the state Justice Department to immediately put on hold a judge's ruling to purge  more than 200,000 voter registrations in the key swing state before it hears from the other side.
lead_paragraph: MADISON, Wis. — A Wisconsin appeals court on Wednesday denied a request from the state Justice Department to immediately put on hold a judge's ruling to purge more than 200,000 voter registrations in the key swing state before it hears from the other side.
headline_main: Wisconsin Appeals Court Delays Ruling on Voter Purge Case
headline_print_headline: Wisconsin Appeals Court Delays Ruling on Voter Purge Case

abstract: A winnowed field of Democratic presidential contenders takes the debate stage Thursday for a sixth and final time in 2019, as candidates seek to convince anxious voters that they are the party's best hope to deny President Donald Trump a second term.
snippet: A winnowed field of Democratic presidential contenders takes the debate stage Thursday for a sixth and final time in 2019, as candidates seek to convince anxious voters that they are the party's best hope to deny President Donald Trump a second te...
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — A winnowed field of Democratic presidential contenders takes the debate stage Thursday for a sixth and final time in 2019, as candidates seek to convince anxious voters that they are the party's best hope to deny President Donald Trump a second term.
headline_main: 2020 Democrats Prepare to Debate in Shadow of Impeachment
headline_print_headline: 2020 Democrats Prepare to Debate in Shadow of Impeachment

headline_main: Impeachment: The House vs. Donald Trump

abstract: The move would prevent migrants convicted of misdemeanors like possessing a fake ID from receiving asylum.
snippet: The move would prevent migrants convicted of misdemeanors like possessing a fake ID from receiving asylum.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration moved on Wednesday to bar immigrants convicted of minor crimes in the United States from obtaining asylum, the latest effort to limit protections extended to those fleeing persecution.
